  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 425°F (220°C).",
    "Season the roast with garlic powder, salt, and pepper.",
    "Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Sear the roast on all sides until browned, about 2-3 minutes per side.",
    "Transfer the skillet to the preheated oven and roast for 20-25 minutes, or until the roast reaches your desired level of doneness.",
    "Whisk together caramel sauce, orange juice, and lemon juice in a small bowl.",
    "Remove the roast from the oven and brush the caramel sauce mixture evenly over the top.",
    "Sprinkle chopped raw almonds over the top of the roast for garnish.",
    "Let the roast rest for 5 minutes before slicing and serving.",
    "Serve warm, garnished with fresh thyme if desired."
